<subSubSection id="3875DC252559BDEA08EDF90DBF3DF5D2" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="20FD22C45E23ED0FA7166046C9227B34" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Distribution and biotope.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E6326E9DD8F5EBF4A2A44B78D08B268" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
All Atlantic coasts of Europe, from Scandinavia, Britain and Ireland, south to the Mediterranean Sea, Morocco (
<bibRefCitation id="96E505568E33F2BD15EAB45E8FA5CA91" author="Kaas, P" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" pagination="89 - 98" title="Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) procured by the CANCAP I-VII expeditions, 1976 - 86." volume="65" year="1991">Kaas 1991</bibRefCitation>
), Azores and Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="2797612D7F9771FBA76971AB665068CF" author="Kaas, P" journalOrPublisher="EJ Brill / W Backhuys Eds., Leiden" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" title="Monograph of living chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora), Vol. 2: Suborder Ischnochitonina: Ischnochitonidae: Schizoplacinae, Callochitoninae &amp; Lepidochitoninae." year="1985 b">Kaas and Van Belle 1985b</bibRefCitation>
). From shallow subtidal to 500 m depth, usually on red algae and other hard substrates (
<bibRefCitation id="CC6922716474BAE1F7D08C58A19DC974" author="Poppe, GT" journalOrPublisher="Verlag Christa Hemmen, Wiesbaden" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" title="European seashells, Vol. 1 (Polyplacophora, Caudofoveata, Solenogastra, Gastropoda)." year="1991">Poppe and Goto 1991</bibRefCitation>
). The animals can be extremely cryptic, grazing on the underside of stones and small boulders where their colours proved good camouflage.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
